text: I did the khans prerelease.

So I'm writing my first article on the 60 to 100 card format idea. Do you think people would be more interested in it structured as "you like to play this archetype/deck in standard/modern/legacy, here is a decklist and why you might like it" or would you rather see it focused on a few commanders suggested in different color combos that would appeal and then a sample decklist of one of the commanders instead?
seems the same other than in the latter you make a few suggestions before diving into one?
sorry i had a hard time parsing your question
Option A: Here is a 60-card deck, here is a commander deck that you might like and why
Option B: Here is a 60-card deck, here are a few different commanders you might like and a sample decklist of one
B
right, so B is the same as A but there is more?
Basically should I focus more on one commander or multiple
Option A would be going deeper into a single commander at a time
A seems super specific. Giving more options is better
Sorry, it made sense it my head when I asked it
but both provide lists, im just confused about whats different
like does B have less of something
As long as you recreate the experience of playing that 60 card deck, do either
or does B just plop the decklist down without explaining it
Option B would give a few separate commanders but not go as deep into each one, option A would be going deep into only 1 commander
k
i like A better given the potential audience of people trying to convert decks maybe
might benefit frmo more depth
but you could still outline some high-level options
“oh, you like turbofog, well here is a angus mackenzie deck. K&T and Kruphix are other options — one sentence each”
i think you should do whatever you want though
Sounds good, I couldn't make up my mind on either so I wanted to see what the consensus was

You could always throw Don's suggestion at the end of your article.
So do in depth on one, and then suggest these other options for consideration
Your article will probably cover the strategy in enough depth they could understand/ figure out where the other commanders lead
Or throw a few suggestions out at the start, but select the one you think is most similar and go deep on that one
